{
  "stem": "24231.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And because there were a lot of Jewish teachers who were also discharged, I got acquainted-- my parents got acquainted with some parents and we formed little circles.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Like, we called-- we used to call them circles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "First, I wanted to-- there was only one Jewish, Jewish school in central Prague but it was all filled up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were too many kids and I had no-- I didn't-- my parents didn't know anybody to get some pull to get into the class.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we formed a circle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went from one house to another.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One day we were in this house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Next day we-- and we got a, a, very good education from that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as my activities, there were some Zionist organizations in Prague.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never belonged to any Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as it says, misery keeps a company, so I tried to seek out a lot of Jewish kids.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this-- the organization was on the other side of Prague, the name was Strasnice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it used to belong to an organization, which was called Hagibor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was under the leadership of a Jewish fellow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His name was Freddy Hirsch.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I used to go over there, and we used to play soccer there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What happened is, I got a pass because the Jews at that-- we were wearing stars and I got a pass on the trolley car.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So from my place, I always used to go to the other part of the-- but I used to, drive-- we used to be able to sit only in the back of the trolley car.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And any time a, a German guy or SS man would come and say, all the Jews out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So all the Jews had to, to get out of the trolley car.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
